# Motion explainer (product default)

- **Ship:** explainer **animation**—illustrations (icons, SVG, raster art), **logic and status symbols** (arrows, braces, grouping, delete/success markers, operators, etc.), and **emphasis motion** (zoom, pan, translate, camera) timed to the argument.
- **Reject:** shots whose main job is **paragraph text** or “title + body copy” readout on camera. That is the same failure family as **static serial readout** (see `component-first-default.mdc`).
- **Roles:** script and structure **inform** what to show; the **primary canvas** is **moving structure**, not walls of plaintext. Prefer `kind`s and views that **spend frames on motion**, not on dumping long strings for the viewer to read.
